<graph edgedefault="undirected"><node id="Multi-Way Decision Statement">
  <data key="d0">Multi-Way Decision Statement</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A multi-way decision statement, such as a switch statement, is a programming construct that allows for branching to different code paths based on the value of a variable or expression.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fb105fc5954ed7ecb73c560e551b6191</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830279</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Loops">
  <data key="d0">Loops</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Loops like while do, repeat until, and for are iterative programming constructs that repeatedly execute a block of code.&lt;SEP&gt;Loops are programming constructs that require specific test cases, especially around boundary conditions, to ensure they function properly.&lt;SEP&gt;Loops are programming constructs used to repeat a block of code, such as 'for', 'while', or 'repeat'.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fb105fc5954ed7ecb73c560e551b6191&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1885c8cabab1027faeb9afbaf3f0ddc5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-52bc4ae0ed75d4c9e063e984a954b88b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830686</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Code Coverage Testing">
  <data key="d0">Code Coverage Testing</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Code coverage testing is a software testing method that involves designing and executing test cases to determine the percentage of code covered by the tests.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fb105fc5954ed7ecb73c560e551b6191</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830279</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Instrumentation Of Code">
  <data key="d0">Instrumentation Of Code</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Instrumentation of code is a technique used in code coverage testing to rebuild the product with libraries provided by tool vendors to track code execution.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fb105fc5954ed7ecb73c560e551b6191</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830280</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Sequential Statements">
  <data key="d0">Sequential Statements</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Sequential statements, such as assignment statements, are a basic prime in structured programming.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fb105fc5954ed7ecb73c560e551b6191</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830280</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Test Engineer">
  <data key="d0">Test Engineer</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">A Test Engineer is responsible for executing and maintaining tests, filing high-quality defects, categorizing defects, adhering to schedules, and developing high-quality documentation.&lt;SEP&gt;A Test Engineer is responsible for selecting and executing test cases, especially in regression testing.&lt;SEP&gt;The test engineers design, develop, and execute tests, develop test harnesses, and set up test laboratories and environments. They also give input to test planning and support maintenance of the test and defect repositories.&lt;SEP&gt;A test engineer is responsible for ensuring effective and productive testing and addressing quality issues.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8d8dfcf969762b4a4e5d97f042d27036&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-56db660e3609aef43610e61aa17e8a81&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fcbf2b63fbccb6dd9180c41126c64053&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4e1d6f42b98e3c56f98bec31ea6b1c40</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831017</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Senior Test Engineer">
  <data key="d0">Senior Test Engineer</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">A Senior Test Engineer helps development staff in debugging and problem isolation, contributes to enhancing testing processes, and generates metrics related to testing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8d8dfcf969762b4a4e5d97f042d27036</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830280</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Decision Statements">
  <data key="d0">Decision Statements</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Decision statements, such as if/then/else statements, are a basic prime in structured programming.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fb105fc5954ed7ecb73c560e551b6191</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830280</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Iterative Constructs">
  <data key="d0">Iterative Constructs</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Iterative constructs, such as while and for loops, are a basic prime in structured programming.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fb105fc5954ed7ecb73c560e551b6191</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830281</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Test Lead">
  <data key="d0">Test Lead</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">A Test Lead reviews test cases and test designs, plans test strategies, allocates tasks, mentors team members, interacts with the development team for debugging, and has overall responsibility for test quality.&lt;SEP&gt;The test lead assists the test manager and works with a team of test engineers on individual projects. He or she may be responsible for duties such as test planning, staff supervision, and status reporting. The test lead also participates in test design, test execution and reporting, technical reviews, customer interaction, and tool training.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8d8dfcf969762b4a4e5d97f042d27036&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fcbf2b63fbccb6dd9180c41126c64053</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830882</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Test Architect">
  <data key="d0">Test Architect</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">A Test Architect possesses in-depth knowledge of testing techniques and methodologies, provides technical assistance and advice to the Test Manager, and can affect change across engineering disciplines.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8d8dfcf969762b4a4e5d97f042d27036</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830282</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Flow Graph">
  <data key="d0">Flow Graph</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A flow graph is a graphical representation of code that shows the sequence of statements, decisions, and loops.&lt;SEP&gt;A flow graph consists of nodes and edges, used to represent a program.&lt;SEP&gt;Flow Graph is a visual representation used in software testing to depict the paths and decision points within a program.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fb105fc5954ed7ecb73c560e551b6191&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4320b5806b340aa80c399ed230ca5ef7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-31605e427568e1b44a7a0bc08c7ec7e9</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831335</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Nodes">
  <data key="d0">Nodes</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Nodes in a flow graph represent sequential statements, decision predicates, and looping predicates.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fb105fc5954ed7ecb73c560e551b6191</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830282</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Test Process">
  <data key="d0">Test Process</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The Test Process involves executing and maintaining tests.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8d8dfcf969762b4a4e5d97f042d27036</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830283</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Test Case">
  <data key="d0">Test Case</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A Test Case is a fundamental element in software testing, designed to verify specific functionalities or conditions of a software product and determine whether the system satisfies requirements or works correctly. It is a detailed procedure and a test-related item that needs a set of criteria to decide whether a test has passed or failed upon execution.

A test case contains test inputs, execution conditions, and expected outputs. Testers execute test cases under a selected set of conditions or variables. The aim of a Test Case is to find the maximum number of defects in software.

Effective test cases contribute to efficient resource use, test reuse, adherence to schedules, and higher software quality. A Test Case is reviewed by the Test Lead.&lt;SEP&gt;A test case is a set of conditions or variables under which a tester will determine whether an application, software system or one of its features is working as it was designed to be working.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8d8dfcf969762b4a4e5d97f042d27036&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6ff2808b9a579f74a66fa6fdc41222f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-56db660e3609aef43610e61aa17e8a81&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1f2f00224294bd5a13c502fab087870d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d1d7014ef279c74a7acb5889dca6440&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0c000d3c006e3afe689c5531f61cede1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4236e7b8427ccbaff16d4b0ef1506341&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-777f4f5fd36fe745076f0229587eef55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a94f41997c5f1aa0c225f8a6c1b0f012</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831318</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Edges">
  <data key="d0">Edges</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Edges in a flow graph represent the transfer of control between nodes, depending on the outcome of conditions in the predicates.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fb105fc5954ed7ecb73c560e551b6191</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830283</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Pos_Sum">
  <data key="d0">Pos_Sum</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">`Pos_sum` is a function that finds the sum of all positive numbers in an integer array.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fb105fc5954ed7ecb73c560e551b6191</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830284</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Test Design">
  <data key="d0">Test Design</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Test Design is reviewed by the Test Lead.&lt;SEP&gt;Test design involves creating test cases and procedures to verify software functionality.&lt;SEP&gt;Test design is the process of designing test cases.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8d8dfcf969762b4a4e5d97f042d27036&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fcbf2b63fbccb6dd9180c41126c64053&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4e1d6f42b98e3c56f98bec31ea6b1c40</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831025</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Debugging">
  <data key="d0">Debugging</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Debugging is a process of identifying and removing errors from software.&lt;SEP&gt;Debugging is the process of locating defects and repairing software.&lt;SEP&gt;Debugging is the process of identifying and removing errors or defects in software code.&lt;SEP&gt;Debugging, also known as fault localization, is the process of locating, repairing, and retesting code after a fault is found.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8d8dfcf969762b4a4e5d97f042d27036&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d1d7014ef279c74a7acb5889dca6440&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ab025a6280cae81005d1ff3a3a08029e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-69c0cfe4a2b7b48410d36c1025bd36b7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831870</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Num_Of_Entries">
  <data key="d0">Num_Of_Entries</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">`Num_of_entries` is an integer input parameter representing the number of elements in an array.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fb105fc5954ed7ecb73c560e551b6191</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830285</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Sume">
  <data key="d0">Sume</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">`Sume` is an integer output parameter representing the sum of positive numbers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fb105fc5954ed7ecb73c560e551b6191</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830285</data>
