<node id="Learnengineering.In">
  <data key="d0">Learnengineering.In</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Learnengineering.In is a website that provides resources and information. Specifically, it offers engineering-related resources and information, making it a valuable platform for learning engineering. The website also serves as a source for additional details on various topics, potentially including software testing. It is often referenced as a place where more information can be found.&lt;SEP&gt;Learnengineering.In is a website providing resources, as indicated by its URL.&lt;SEP&gt;Learnengineering.In is a resource or website providing additional information related to the content.&lt;SEP&gt;Learnengineering.In is a website providing content related to software testing.&lt;SEP&gt;A website providing more information.&lt;SEP&gt;Learnengineering.In is a website providing information, as indicated by its repeated mention.&lt;SEP&gt;Learnengineering.in is a website that provides resources and information.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8d8dfcf969762b4a4e5d97f042d27036&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b4ab47d35eeaee4c5eceb6f8589fa909&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4320b5806b340aa80c399ed230ca5ef7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2ae86184847a25f93edb5f375e4378fc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a9004c9fb37134adfd3b872db4e4a036&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6293aec7ed87430ba4236ef6fa4fc8a2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a8c81f7a1e1c30a9a414bb702063e460&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-730afa5a03e337a9a1b2ed3ad640133d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-31605e427568e1b44a7a0bc08c7ec7e9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dbbf2f5da383a1fc924d351d3652477f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d54ee8dd0e2b5ff1654ab561620b6c44&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac3c02729685274cd9387cadef0dc333&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3dbe431461265e42abb2f74972788b5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed0e4731c3296bc5ba3ae5edf4cd9631</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831762</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Test Manager">
  <data key="d0">Test Manager</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8d8dfcf969762b4a4e5d97f042d27036&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fcbf2b63fbccb6dd9180c41126c64053&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ab025a6280cae81005d1ff3a3a08029e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7c7f1235e8106bb7153b375709adaf33</data>
  <data key="d2">The Test Architect provides technical assistance and advice to the Test Manager.&lt;SEP&gt;The test manager is the central person concerned with all aspects of testing and quality issues. The test manager is usually responsible for test policy making, customer interaction, test planning, test documentation, controlling and monitoring of tests, training, test tool acquisition, participation in inspections and walkthroughs, reviewing test work, the test repository, and staffing issues such as hiring, firing, and evaluation of the test team members.&lt;SEP&gt;The Test Manager is responsible for coordinating test planning, guiding plan development, and working with the project manager.&lt;SEP&gt;The Test Manager uses collected data for presentation and discussion at project status meetings and produces reports to inform management of test progress.</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831860</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Customer">
  <data key="d0">Customer</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The customer fills out a check and receives cash from an official.&lt;SEP&gt;The Customer is a stakeholder that the testing strategy should be flexible to.&lt;SEP&gt;The customer is the entity for which the testing services organization provides services.&lt;SEP&gt;The Customer is the entity that contracts the testing service organization for testing services.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c3bed4b901712f25dcd4883811a56a9f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c7cd0ee78ddf28561be524a34f8204f8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7c06066fef21175272ed95dcceb2a37a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-071f8c515f1feaf347a890f589abbdf1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830752</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Official">
  <data key="d0">Official</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">The official verifies the balance and provides the customer with cash.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c3bed4b901712f25dcd4883811a56a9f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830306</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="System Response">
  <data key="d0">System Response</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The computer gives the balance in the account.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c3bed4b901712f25dcd4883811a56a9f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830306</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Actor">
  <data key="d0">Actor</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The actor is concerned only about getting cash, not the actions of the official or the commands used to interact with the computer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c3bed4b901712f25dcd4883811a56a9f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830307</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Agent">
  <data key="d0">Agent</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">The agent is concerned about whether they will get money or not, not the logic of how the computer works.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c3bed4b901712f25dcd4883811a56a9f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830307</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Use Case Model">
  <data key="d0">Use Case Model</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Testers using the use case model complement each other's testing of the business and implementation aspects of the product.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c3bed4b901712f25dcd4883811a56a9f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830307</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Automated System">
  <data key="d0">Automated System</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">In a completely automated system, use cases can be written without considering the agent portion.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c3bed4b901712f25dcd4883811a56a9f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
