</node>
<node id="ATM">
  <data key="d0">ATM</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">The ATM is used for cash withdrawal.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c3bed4b901712f25dcd4883811a56a9f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830308</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Defect Bash">
  <data key="d0">Defect Bash</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Defect bash is an ad hoc testing method where people performing different roles in an organization test the product together.&lt;SEP&gt;Defect bash is a testing activity or session focused on finding defects.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c3bed4b901712f25dcd4883811a56a9f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ef2e90aeeaaea52d08d7eed63146a5f5</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830716</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Organization">
  <data key="d0">Organization</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">An entity where different roles test the product together during defect bash.&lt;SEP&gt;The organization designates who should review the test plans.&lt;SEP&gt;The organization is referenced as having competent people to review the test plan.&lt;SEP&gt;An organization develops a review plan template applicable to all software projects.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c3bed4b901712f25dcd4883811a56a9f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-31e1a59391bc5c57ad4d5941cffbeb6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-976050e1c7ac2fe8f9cfeac3ea4fb575&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-226d94c07ca09316fdcba5b872e40b9d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-52bc934fcfeec89646ffbc42ac44a30a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831726</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="IEEE Standard">
  <data key="d0">IEEE Standard</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The IEEE Standard is an organization that provides standards for software test documentation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-71bc9a6310b266a0a41d358c602d50e1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830309</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Test Design Specification">
  <data key="d0">Test Design Specification</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">A test deliverable that specifies the requirements of the test approach, links to test cases and procedures, and describes pass/fail criteria.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-71bc9a6310b266a0a41d358c602d50e1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830309</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="R.M.D. Engineering College">
  <data key="d0">R.M.D. Engineering College</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">R.M.D. Engineering College is an educational institution, notably through its IT Department. The IT Department is actively involved in creating and documenting materials related to software testing, including topics such as Beta Testing. The department is frequently identified as the source of these documents, as stated in the document header and, in some cases, specifically on Page 21 and Page 4 of the documents. Thus, the college, via its IT Department, provides the context for these software testing documents.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c3bed4b901712f25dcd4883811a56a9f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1a701e33391919caf4151b2a9d6fa069&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-56db660e3609aef43610e61aa17e8a81&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-71fc4f34702301e4dd6c1ae7beda783b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89e0667e9e77a3e174bbf9f89dd8f482&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9f460ca10683bf9cef13145da1c4fc71&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9ea23d51412441d95fd9957313b3d478&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c2d7d142472e7acf420224383c99b13b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b7ff6ae81d2cbdd2fa63a7c1554d2eaf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d95d5a03291c8ae4834c72b31a85edc7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fb22ba0e1a3621e7dc6f377089c45524&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0682a23253488e1a8adf8e634de7e049&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ef2e90aeeaaea52d08d7eed63146a5f5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2ae86184847a25f93edb5f375e4378fc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b6de8307f33f851b1e62ada0a1e5b961&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0ad834ab92932d983e93d86d224421e9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0c000d3c006e3afe689c5531f61cede1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8139eb8fe9a7e279b24055af3d6cb375&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bc034242c01926773d32a19ffb90ce40&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3aa46a63f1b9b0d523911f6df64c6dde&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d01d5a91698d48273a7f4da4a262d5a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ba6b80bf01467ce55688de3f4b3e1921&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6293aec7ed87430ba4236ef6fa4fc8a2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6aa29d254f483e087581868e6c7acd2c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d4600873a7185719f33d700ae5a5d121&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-55856660a2522d1670370f74ea265c8e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dac674a5a618326bac489f8124a35c69&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-72174c906a600ada847dff60ecc94505&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-226d94c07ca09316fdcba5b872e40b9d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3225239af0275d5998bfbd97b0931848&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-00fde9a7a0d6d603361efdace01d913f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4eb81c1b056c3ffba100a30fb6ddc42f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f9a1e0b0e37c96741aefa49dc8030cdc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90608f1fe255e95bf5a4da4744ec4c35&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c865455d56f087310ad4a2872dcee595&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-69c0cfe4a2b7b48410d36c1025bd36b7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831874</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="IT Department">
  <data key="d0">IT Department</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The IT Department is a department within R.M.D. Engineering College and plays a crucial role in the college's operations. It is responsible for or associated with various documents and content, including study material related to Software Testing. The IT Department is credited with creating or being responsible for content provided by R.M.D. Engineering College, specifically documenting information related to Software Testing. In particular, it presents information and provides documents on Software Testing.&lt;SEP&gt;The IT Department is part of R.M.D. Engineering College, mentioned in the document header.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c3bed4b901712f25dcd4883811a56a9f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1a701e33391919caf4151b2a9d6fa069&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5dc410bc2f23656e00ef58bd19840cb4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-56db660e3609aef43610e61aa17e8a81&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-71fc4f34702301e4dd6c1ae7beda783b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89e0667e9e77a3e174bbf9f89dd8f482&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9ea23d51412441d95fd9957313b3d478&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b7ff6ae81d2cbdd2fa63a7c1554d2eaf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fb22ba0e1a3621e7dc6f377089c45524&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2ae86184847a25f93edb5f375e4378fc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4a2a0fc342861ce4f51a3e5784bf82da&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b6de8307f33f851b1e62ada0a1e5b961&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0ad834ab92932d983e93d86d224421e9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-033cfdf9a6b36a9a16d2b1d936959166&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1f50a0acff86b61f2aebdc6201bedb80&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0c000d3c006e3afe689c5531f61cede1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-50ee503f2fae49523a55b9fcdc5df8d1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bc034242c01926773d32a19ffb90ce40&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d01d5a91698d48273a7f4da4a262d5a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2b3bde5b1c616694ba3017923a6d3344&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d4600873a7185719f33d700ae5a5d121&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-55856660a2522d1670370f74ea265c8e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2e450de8294677410b0dfa671b57c74f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cfbe20c55205b7267c83b935777d953d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-72174c906a600ada847dff60ecc94505&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-226d94c07ca09316fdcba5b872e40b9d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-00fde9a7a0d6d603361efdace01d913f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-52bc934fcfeec89646ffbc42ac44a30a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed0e4731c3296bc5ba3ae5edf4cd9631&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f9a1e0b0e37c96741aefa49dc8030cdc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7c7f1235e8106bb7153b375709adaf33&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-69c0cfe4a2b7b48410d36c1025bd36b7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831873</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Test Plan">
  <data key="d0">Test Plan</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">A test plan is a document that serves as the foundation for a testing project. It is typically prepared by the testing group prior to test execution and is reviewed and approved by competent individuals and authorities within the organization.

The test plan outlines the strategy, objectives, schedule, estimation, deliverables, and resources required for testing a software product. It contains a general description of the approach to be used to test each item, including the scope and design, and the relationships between unit tests.

Furthermore, the test plan includes a cost component and specifies deviations and the reasons for these deviations. In essence, it outlines the approach, resources, and schedule of testing activities.&lt;SEP&gt;A document referenced by the Test Item Transmittal Report, outlining the planned testing activities.&lt;SEP&gt;A test plan is developed from a template and changes are made only after approval.&lt;SEP&gt;The test plan specifies the expected state to which the current testing efforts are compared.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-71bc9a6310b266a0a41d358c602d50e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-31e1a59391bc5c57ad4d5941cffbeb6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-576c3b5853abc31c233b7f55290db336&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-976050e1c7ac2fe8f9cfeac3ea4fb575&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0ad834ab92932d983e93d86d224421e9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1f50a0acff86b61f2aebdc6201bedb80&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2b3c34fc8c737800e72c4ba3dd2c8eff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d54ee8dd0e2b5ff1654ab561620b6c44&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac3c02729685274cd9387cadef0dc333&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-994f0b8030636c42759ae6d6ee2baddc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cfbe20c55205b7267c83b935777d953d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831545</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Test Cases">
  <data key="d0">Test Cases</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Test cases are a series of documents, often associated with a test design specification, that provide detailed instructions for executing tests and validating results to verify the functionality of a software product. They define the inputs, execution conditions, and expected results for testing, and can be implemented manually or through automated test scripts. These cases are written to exercise the different functions of code and are used to achieve function coverage, including input data and expected outputs to verify the functionality of a software unit.

Designed and reviewed for unit testing, test cases represent a set of conditions or variables under which a tester determines whether a system satisfies requirements or functions correctly. They are designed using specific techniques for the units being tested, and are ideally individual test scenarios that should be independent and selectively executable. Test cases are also used to ensure basic functionalities work and are often packaged into a smoke test suite. Some test cases are automated test cases taken from TCDB (potentially a Test Case Database) and executed by a testing framework. The ability to plan, design, and execute test cases is considered a technical skill. Furthermore, test cases are associated with the test items involved in the test incident report.&lt;SEP&gt;Test cases are transformed from the columns in the decision table.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-71bc9a6310b266a0a41d358c602d50e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4320b5806b340aa80c399ed230ca5ef7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-976050e1c7ac2fe8f9cfeac3ea4fb575&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0682a23253488e1a8adf8e634de7e049&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-08aa6af3aad54d106fc55a5710f36151&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b6de8307f33f851b1e62ada0a1e5b961&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-413abe27441aa74b0b434e98bea575fe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-750a18a20f82fd7a983c3b7f203c7a6f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42669b4fcb6bce2882145c03df26e5f5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d4600873a7185719f33d700ae5a5d121&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2b3c34fc8c737800e72c4ba3dd2c8eff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3225239af0275d5998bfbd97b0931848&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d460fa457eb3a013c4e2949dd7c5d083&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3dbe431461265e42abb2f74972788b5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed0e4731c3296bc5ba3ae5edf4cd9631&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f9a1e0b0e37c96741aefa49dc8030cdc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dadd5fedffda581a4f86164ce8358084&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b1985b2f00f63e1c64f0933bd04e3e13</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831822</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Test Procedures">
  <data key="d0">Test Procedures</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Steps necessary to execute tests.&lt;SEP&gt;Test procedures are steps required to execute test cases during unit testing.&lt;SEP&gt;Test Procedures are associated with the test items involved in the test incident report.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-71bc9a6310b266a0a41d358c602d50e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0682a23253488e1a8adf8e634de7e049&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2b3c34fc8c737800e72c4ba3dd2c8eff</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831397</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Test Case Specification">
  <data key="d0">Test Case Specification</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">A series of documents that defines the test cases required to execute the test items named in the associated test design specification.&lt;SEP&gt;The test case specification, designed by the testing team based on the test plan, outlines the purpose of the test, items being tested, environment setup, input data, execution steps, expected results, and a comparison step.&lt;SEP&gt;Test case specification includes the input or the output that was not specified correctly.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-71bc9a6310b266a0a41d358c602d50e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-976050e1c7ac2fe8f9cfeac3ea4fb575&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-08aa6af3aad54d106fc55a5710f36151</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830727</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cash">
  <data key="d0">Cash</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c3bed4b901712f25dcd4883811a56a9f</data>
  <data key="d2">The actor's primary concern is getting cash.</data>
  <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830312</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Test Items">
  <data key="d0">Test Items</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Items and features to be tested.&lt;SEP&gt;The test items are involved in the test procedures, test cases, and test log associated with this report.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-71bc9a6310b266a0a41d358c602d50e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2b3c34fc8c737800e72c4ba3dd2c8eff</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831397</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Input Specifications">
  <data key="d0">Input Specifications</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">The actual inputs needed to execute the test.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-71bc9a6310b266a0a41d358c602d50e1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830313</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Money">
  <data key="d0">Money</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c3bed4b901712f25dcd4883811a56a9f</data>
  <data key="d2">The agent is concerned about whether they will get money.</data>
  <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830314</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Pass/Fail Criteria">
  <data key="d0">Pass/Fail Criteria</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The specific criteria to be used for determining whether the item has passed/failed a test.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-71bc9a6310b266a0a41d358c602d50e1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830314</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Approach Refinements">
  <data key="d0">Approach Refinements</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Describes how test results will be analyzed and discusses the relationships among the associated test cases.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-71bc9a6310b266a0a41d358c602d50e1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830315</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Testing">
  <data key="d0">Testing</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c3bed4b901712f25dcd4883811a56a9f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5dc410bc2f23656e00ef58bd19840cb4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d1d7014ef279c74a7acb5889dca6440&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f4172dd84636c7dab653ead0e84fbdaf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-033cfdf9a6b36a9a16d2b1d936959166&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-994f0b8030636c42759ae6d6ee2baddc</data>
  <data key="d2">Testers use the use case model to test the product's business and implementation aspects.&lt;SEP&gt;A software development sub-process that needs improvement and evaluation, and a group of procedures carried out to evaluate some aspect of a piece of software.&lt;SEP&gt;Testing is a software quality assurance method and career that requires a holistic understanding of the product and multiple domains.&lt;SEP&gt;Testing refers to the software testing process, which includes various types of testing (integration, system) and requires service level agreements with development.</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831473</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Test Design Specification Identifier">
  <data key="d0">Test Design Specification Identifier</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">A unique identifier assigned to each test design specification, referencing its associated test plan.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-71bc9a6310b266a0a41d358c602d50e1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830316</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Features To Be Tested">
  <data key="d0">Features To Be Tested</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Test items, features, and combinations of features covered by a test design specification.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-71bc9a6310b266a0a41d358c602d50e1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830316</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Test Case Identification">
  <data key="d0">Test Case Identification</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Associates each test design specification with a set of test cases and procedures.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-71bc9a6310b266a0a41d358c602d50e1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830317</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Test Case Specification Identifier">
  <data key="d0">Test Case Specification Identifier</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">A unique identifier assigned to each test case specification.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-71bc9a6310b266a0a41d358c602d50e1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830317</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Usability Testing">
  <data key="d0">Usability Testing</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Usability Testing is a method to determine the extent to which a software product is understood, easy to learn, easy to operate, and attractive to users under specified conditions.&lt;SEP&gt;Usability Testing is a method used to find bugs and potholes, fix problems before application releases, and can be modified to support other types of testing.&lt;SEP&gt;Usability Testing is a type of testing done from an end-user's perspective to determine if the system is easily usable.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4ab47d35eeaee4c5eceb6f8589fa909&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2ae86184847a25f93edb5f375e4378fc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ba6b80bf01467ce55688de3f4b3e1921</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831202</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Software Product">
  <data key="d0">Software Product</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">The Software Product refers to the application being tested for usability.&lt;SEP&gt;Software Product benefits from testers detecting defects and evaluating quality early in the software life cycle.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4ab47d35eeaee4c5eceb6f8589fa909&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-09aff991601cb8d11a8b32035d5ed5c8</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831754</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="System">
  <data key="d0">System</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The system requires the user to go through multiple steps to print a Financial Update Report.&lt;SEP&gt;System is a testing phase.&lt;SEP&gt;A system is a complete set of integrated components delivering product functionality and features.&lt;SEP&gt;System is a level of software testing.&lt;SEP&gt;System refers to the software or application being tested as a whole.&lt;SEP&gt;The system has requirements that the application should work within.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4ab47d35eeaee4c5eceb6f8589fa909&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-57b5bdf87e3c8352e48d198a65913eb1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ef2e90aeeaaea52d08d7eed63146a5f5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4e1d6f42b98e3c56f98bec31ea6b1c40&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bc034242c01926773d32a19ffb90ce40&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3225239af0275d5998bfbd97b0931848</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831588</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Financial Update Report">
  <data key="d0">Financial Update Report</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">The Financial Update Report is a report that a user needs to print every 30 minutes as an example in usability testing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4ab47d35eeaee4c5eceb6f8589fa909</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830327</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="System Testing">
  <data key="d0">System Testing</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">System Testing is a level during which usability testing is normally performed.&lt;SEP&gt;System testing is testing conducted on complete, integrated products to evaluate system compliance with requirements.&lt;SEP&gt;System testing is the process of testing the complete and integrated software system.&lt;SEP&gt;System testing is a type of software testing.&lt;SEP&gt;System testing is the process of testing a fully integrated system to verify that it meets specified requirements.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4ab47d35eeaee4c5eceb6f8589fa909&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ef2e90aeeaaea52d08d7eed63146a5f5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-adc0f944e298fc1492f619b8a593d383&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-994f0b8030636c42759ae6d6ee2baddc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-226d94c07ca09316fdcba5b872e40b9d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831581</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Acceptance Testing">
  <data key="d0">Acceptance Testing</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Acceptance Testing is a level during which usability testing is normally performed.&lt;SEP&gt;Acceptance Testing is a phase done by the customers to check whether the product is ready for use in the real-life environment.&lt;SEP&gt;Acceptance testing is conducted by product management / product marketing&lt;SEP&gt;Acceptance Testing is a form of both Alpha and Beta Testing.&lt;SEP&gt;Acceptance Testing is a type of testing performed after System Testing to determine if a system satisfies its acceptance criteria.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4ab47d35eeaee4c5eceb6f8589fa909&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-57b5bdf87e3c8352e48d198a65913eb1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-adc0f944e298fc1492f619b8a593d383&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-588cab56860b1b61b223c01b7307a5a5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-226d94c07ca09316fdcba5b872e40b9d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831573</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="User Acceptance Testing">
  <data key="d0">User Acceptance Testing</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">User Acceptance Testing is distinct from Usability Testing.&lt;SEP&gt;User Acceptance Testing is a type of testing performed by the end-users of the software.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4ab47d35eeaee4c5eceb6f8589fa909&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-226d94c07ca09316fdcba5b872e40b9d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831577</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="User Interface">
  <data key="d0">User Interface</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The User Interface, including its look and feel, is distinct from Usability Testing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4ab47d35eeaee4c5eceb6f8589fa909</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830329</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Website">
  <data key="d0">Website</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">A website needs to have a realistic load time, adequate text-to-background contrast, readable font size and spacing, and a custom designed Not Found page.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4ab47d35eeaee4c5eceb6f8589fa909</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830329</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
