<node id="Inspection Report">
  <data key="d0">Inspection Report</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">The inspection report is a document signed by all reviewers, summarizing defects, problems, attendees, and measures.&lt;SEP&gt;The Inspection Report contains data on the number of participants, meeting duration, item size, preparation time, reviewed item status, rework effort estimate, and rework completion date.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1a701e33391919caf4151b2a9d6fa069&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c2d7d142472e7acf420224383c99b13b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830610</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Defect Report">
  <data key="d0">Defect Report</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">A defect report is an output of an inspection that details the defects found.&lt;SEP&gt;The Defect Report contains a description of the defects, the defect type, severity level, and the location of each defect.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1a701e33391919caf4151b2a9d6fa069&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c2d7d142472e7acf420224383c99b13b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830610</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Software Item">
