</node>
<node id="Verification">
  <data key="d0">Verification</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The process of evaluating a software system or component to determine whether the products of a given development phase satisfy the conditions imposed at the start of that phase.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5dc410bc2f23656e00ef58bd19840cb4</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830358</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Validation">
  <data key="d0">Validation</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The process of evaluating a software system or component during, or at the end of, the development cycle in order to determine whether it satisfies specified requirements.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5dc410bc2f23656e00ef58bd19840cb4</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830359</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Software">
  <data key="d0">Software</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">A piece of product that testing intends to evaluate some aspect of it.&lt;SEP&gt;Programs and other operating information used by a computer.&lt;SEP&gt;Software refers to the programs necessary for the tests.&lt;SEP&gt;Software is a resource needed for unit test.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5dc410bc2f23656e00ef58bd19840cb4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-194ddef519cf128899a2be4c3247d7cc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-31e1a59391bc5c57ad4d5941cffbeb6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c7b18e88c7970da3d28ba996629ad181&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7814e3a12bbf4d4dc88df26f6fc2b9f0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42669b4fcb6bce2882145c03df26e5f5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4eb81c1b056c3ffba100a30fb6ddc42f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831293</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="R.M.D.Engineering College">
  <data key="d0">R.M.D.Engineering College</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">R.M.D.Engineering College is an educational institution, specifically an engineering college, that houses an IT Department. The IT Department of R.M.D.Engineering College provides information and produces documents related to software testing. This association is evidenced by a document on software testing principles produced by the IT Department, which also mentions R.M.D.Engineering College. Notably, Page 9 of this document was also produced by the IT Department. The college's IT Department serves as the context for presenting software testing material.&lt;SEP&gt;R.M.D.Engineering College is the institution associated with the IT Department and the document.&lt;SEP&gt;R.M.D.Engineering College is an educational institution, specifically its IT Department.&lt;SEP&gt;R.M.D.Engineering College's IT Department produced the document on software testing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5dc410bc2f23656e00ef58bd19840cb4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-57b5bdf87e3c8352e48d198a65913eb1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1f2f00224294bd5a13c502fab087870d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c7b18e88c7970da3d28ba996629ad181&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d1d7014ef279c74a7acb5889dca6440&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-033cfdf9a6b36a9a16d2b1d936959166&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1f50a0acff86b61f2aebdc6201bedb80&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0bc02d92c94be7170edbcd55893256aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ab025a6280cae81005d1ff3a3a08029e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7814e3a12bbf4d4dc88df26f6fc2b9f0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-777f4f5fd36fe745076f0229587eef55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2b3bde5b1c616694ba3017923a6d3344&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2e450de8294677410b0dfa671b57c74f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cfbe20c55205b7267c83b935777d953d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-be51d63afa736d2292bcd95d0d343101&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-52bc934fcfeec89646ffbc42ac44a30a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed0e4731c3296bc5ba3ae5edf4cd9631&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7c7f1235e8106bb7153b375709adaf33</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831860</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Professional Engineer">
  <data key="d0">Professional Engineer</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">A licensed engineer with formal designations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5dc410bc2f23656e00ef58bd19840cb4</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830360</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Software Development Process">
  <data key="d0">Software Development Process</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The overarching methodology within which testing is an integral part.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5dc410bc2f23656e00ef58bd19840cb4</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830361</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Defect">
  <data key="d0">Defect</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A Defect, in the context of software development, represents a flaw, error, or issue present within the software. These defects can manifest as missing, incorrect, or superfluous elements, or deviations that negatively impact the software's functionality, performance, reliability, or security. They cause the software to produce incorrect, unexpected, unintended, or otherwise undesirable results.

Defects are formally documented, often by a scribe, and subsequently addressed and fixed by the original author of the code. Test cases, particularly those within a specific equivalence class, and test adequacy criteria can help to identify and reveal these underlying flaws. The process of identifying, fixing, and testing defects is crucial to ensuring software quality.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-56db660e3609aef43610e61aa17e8a81&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c584edf6e5f2b8db471597d14e5d0bd0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c2d7d142472e7acf420224383c99b13b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1f2f00224294bd5a13c502fab087870d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d1d7014ef279c74a7acb5889dca6440&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e67f594ae3047aebaed5c7bf8c5ee26&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-777f4f5fd36fe745076f0229587eef55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-31605e427568e1b44a7a0bc08c7ec7e9</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831342</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Regression Testing">
  <data key="d0">Regression Testing</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Regression Testing is a type of software testing used to confirm that recent program or code changes have not adversely affected existing features.&lt;SEP&gt;Regression testing takes place in the development of future releases of a software product.&lt;SEP&gt;Regression testing is performed by all test teams.&lt;SEP&gt;Regression testing is a type of software testing that verifies that bug fixes do not negatively impact existing functionality and that the application continues to meet system requirements.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-56db660e3609aef43610e61aa17e8a81&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-576c3b5853abc31c233b7f55290db336&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-adc0f944e298fc1492f619b8a593d383&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3225239af0275d5998bfbd97b0931848</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831581</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Automated Regression Testing">
  <data key="d0">Automated Regression Testing</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Automated Regression Testing involves using tools to automate the execution of regression test cases, saving time and effort.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-56db660e3609aef43610e61aa17e8a81</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830367</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Priority-0 Test Cases">
  <data key="d0">Priority-0 Test Cases</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Priority-0 Test Cases are the highest priority test cases that must be executed in regression testing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-56db660e3609aef43610e61aa17e8a81</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830368</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Priority-1 Test Cases">
  <data key="d0">Priority-1 Test Cases</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Priority-1 Test Cases are high-priority test cases that must be executed in regression testing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-56db660e3609aef43610e61aa17e8a81</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830368</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Priority-2 Test Cases">
  <data key="d0">Priority-2 Test Cases</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Priority-2 Test Cases are medium-priority test cases that may be selectively executed in regression testing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-56db660e3609aef43610e61aa17e8a81</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830368</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Regression Test Bed">
  <data key="d0">Regression Test Bed</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Regression Test Bed is a collection of test cases used repeatedly to ensure that changes to software have not introduced new defects.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-56db660e3609aef43610e61aa17e8a81</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830369</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Code Reviews">
  <data key="d0">Code Reviews</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Code Reviews are the inspection of code by individuals other than the author to detect defects and improve code quality.&lt;SEP&gt;Code reviews involve examining code for defects and adherence to standards.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-56db660e3609aef43610e61aa17e8a81&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4e1d6f42b98e3c56f98bec31ea6b1c40</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831028</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Criticality">
  <data key="d0">Criticality</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Criticality refers to the severity level of a defect or issue, impacting the prioritization of testing and fixes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-56db660e3609aef43610e61aa17e8a81</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830369</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Impact">
  <data key="d0">Impact</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Impact assesses the extent to which a defect or fix affects the overall system or functionality.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-56db660e3609aef43610e61aa17e8a81</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830370</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Alternative Methodologies">
  <data key="d0">Alternative Methodologies</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Alternative Methodologies are a set of different strategies for regression testing including Regress all, Priority based regression, Regress changes, Random regression, and Context based dynamic regression.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-56db660e3609aef43610e61aa17e8a81</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830370</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Regress All">
  <data key="d0">Regress All</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Regress All is a regression testing methodology where all test cases are executed.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-56db660e3609aef43610e61aa17e8a81</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830370</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Priority Based Regression">
  <data key="d0">Priority Based Regression</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Priority Based Regression is a regression testing methodology where test cases are prioritized and executed based on their priority.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-56db660e3609aef43610e61aa17e8a81</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830371</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Regress Changes">
  <data key="d0">Regress Changes</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Regress Changes is a regression testing methodology where only the test cases related to the changed code are executed.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-56db660e3609aef43610e61aa17e8a81</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
