<node id="Cyclomatic Complexity">
  <data key="d0">Cyclomatic Complexity</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Cyclomatic complexity is a metric that quantifies the complexity of a program.&lt;SEP&gt;Cyclomatic complexity is a metric used in white box testing to measure the complexity of a program.&lt;SEP&gt;Cyclomatic Complexity is a metric used to measure the complexity of a program by quantifying the number of independent paths in its flow graph.&lt;SEP&gt;Cyclomatic complexity is a measure of the structural complexity of code.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4320b5806b340aa80c399ed230ca5ef7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4236e7b8427ccbaff16d4b0ef1506341&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-31605e427568e1b44a7a0bc08c7ec7e9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed0e4731c3296bc5ba3ae5edf4cd9631</data>
