</node>
<node id="Laboratory Space">
  <data key="d0">Laboratory Space</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Laboratory space refers to the physical location for testing.&lt;SEP&gt;Laboratory space is a space containing the equipment that needs to be reserved.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-31e1a59391bc5c57ad4d5941cffbeb6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-750a18a20f82fd7a983c3b7f203c7a6f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831090</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Risks">
  <data key="d0">Risks</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Risks are potential negative impacts on project goals associated with testing efforts.&lt;SEP&gt;Risks are potential problems or uncertainties that could affect the success of the project.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-31e1a59391bc5c57ad4d5941cffbeb6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51f22a0f26d6d401d4a1e4f700c30a8e</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830970</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Contingencies">
  <data key="d0">Contingencies</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Contingencies are plans developed to be activated if risks occur during testing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-31e1a59391bc5c57ad4d5941cffbeb6b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830462</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Project Manager">
  <data key="d0">Project Manager</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">The project manager is responsible for estimating testing costs in consultation with developers and testers.&lt;SEP&gt;The project manager is mentioned as someone independent of the authority approving the test plan.&lt;SEP&gt;The Project Manager works with the test manager to coordinate activities.&lt;SEP&gt;The project manager is responsible for overseeing the test plan development, especially if there is no separate testing group.&lt;SEP&gt;The Project Manager publishes status reports that are distributed to upper management.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-31e1a59391bc5c57ad4d5941cffbeb6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-976050e1c7ac2fe8f9cfeac3ea4fb575&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ab025a6280cae81005d1ff3a3a08029e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d54ee8dd0e2b5ff1654ab561620b6c44&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7c7f1235e8106bb7153b375709adaf33</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831864</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Testing Group">
  <data key="d0">Testing Group</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The testing group is responsible for preparing the test plan.&lt;SEP&gt;A testing group is a team independent of the development group that carries out testing to ensure software quality.&lt;SEP&gt;The testing group is a team within an organization responsible for various testing activities.&lt;SEP&gt;A testing group is a specialized team established within an organization for testing purposes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-31e1a59391bc5c57ad4d5941cffbeb6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1f2f00224294bd5a13c502fab087870d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4e1d6f42b98e3c56f98bec31ea6b1c40&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3dbe431461265e42abb2f74972788b5f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831723</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Test Environment">
  <data key="d0">Test Environment</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">The test environment is the setup required to support the tests.&lt;SEP&gt;Test environment may include a database.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-31e1a59391bc5c57ad4d5941cffbeb6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-08aa6af3aad54d106fc55a5710f36151</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830727</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Test Results">
  <data key="d0">Test Results</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Test results are recorded and analyzed as part of the testing process.&lt;SEP&gt;Test results are reported after test execution.&lt;SEP&gt;Test results are the outcomes of running tests, which testers inspect to determine if the software passes or fails.&lt;SEP&gt;Test results are recorded in a format such as a summary work sheet.&lt;SEP&gt;Test Results refers to the data and findings obtained from the execution of test cases.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-31e1a59391bc5c57ad4d5941cffbeb6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-576c3b5853abc31c233b7f55290db336&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1f2f00224294bd5a13c502fab087870d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-08aa6af3aad54d106fc55a5710f36151&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-777f4f5fd36fe745076f0229587eef55</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831246</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Testing Costs">
  <data key="d0">Testing Costs</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Testing costs include planning, hardware, software, environment support, execution, analysis, and tear-down costs.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-31e1a59391bc5c57ad4d5941cffbeb6b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830467</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Schedules">
  <data key="d0">Schedules</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-31e1a59391bc5c57ad4d5941cffbeb6b</data>
  <data key="d2">Schedules specify the use of staff for testing activities.</data>
  <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830467</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Test Logs">
  <data key="d0">Test Logs</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Test logs contain information about test execution.&lt;SEP&gt;Test Logs are documents that result from testing.&lt;SEP&gt;Test Logs are test-related documents required for recording test results.&lt;SEP&gt;Test logs are examined to understand the problems occurring during testing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-576c3b5853abc31c233b7f55290db336&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-750a18a20f82fd7a983c3b7f203c7a6f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42669b4fcb6bce2882145c03df26e5f5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cfbe20c55205b7267c83b935777d953d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831544</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Test Summary Report">
  <data key="d0">Test Summary Report</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">A test summary report is produced on test cycle completion and provides insights about the fitness of the product for release.&lt;SEP&gt;The Test Summary Report records the causes of failure and summarizes testing activities for all units covered by the unit test plan.&lt;SEP&gt;Test summary report includes forms with test results.&lt;SEP&gt;Test Summary Report is a document that results from testing.&lt;SEP&gt;A test summary report is prepared when testing is complete, summarizing the results of testing efforts.&lt;SEP&gt;The test summary report is prepared after testing is complete and used in project postmortems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-576c3b5853abc31c233b7f55290db336&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d95d5a03291c8ae4834c72b31a85edc7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-08aa6af3aad54d106fc55a5710f36151&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-750a18a20f82fd7a983c3b7f203c7a6f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2b3c34fc8c737800e72c4ba3dd2c8eff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cfbe20c55205b7267c83b935777d953d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831546</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Product Release Criteria">
  <data key="d0">Product Release Criteria</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Product release criteria are based on defect identification, severity, and impact, as well as the risks of releasing the product with existing defects.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-576c3b5853abc31c233b7f55290db336</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830469</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Ieee Standard For Software Test Documentation">
  <data key="d0">Ieee Standard For Software Test Documentation</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">The IEEE Standard for Software Test Documentation describes documents related to testing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-576c3b5853abc31c233b7f55290db336</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830471</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Test Log">
  <data key="d0">Test Log</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">The test log is a diary of events during tests, prepared by the person executing the tests.&lt;SEP&gt;Test log contains the dates and names of test log authors for each event and activity.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-576c3b5853abc31c233b7f55290db336&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2b3c34fc8c737800e72c4ba3dd2c8eff</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831395</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Test Incident Documents">
  <data key="d0">Test Incident Documents</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Test incident documents, along with test logs, help prevent incorrect decisions based on incomplete or erroneous test results.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-576c3b5853abc31c233b7f55290db336</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830472</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Test Costs">
  <data key="d0">Test Costs</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-31e1a59391bc5c57ad4d5941cffbeb6b</data>
  <data key="d2">The test planner estimates test costs.</data>
  <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830473</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Reuse Library">
  <data key="d0">Reuse Library</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Code from a reuse library is sometimes reused.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-576c3b5853abc31c233b7f55290db336</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830474</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Test Log Identifier">
  <data key="d0">Test Log Identifier</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Each test log should have a unique identifier.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-576c3b5853abc31c233b7f55290db336</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830475</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Description">
  <data key="d0">Description</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">The description includes the items being tested, their version/revision number, and their associated Test Item/Transmittal Report, as well as the testing environment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-576c3b5853abc31c233b7f55290db336</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830475</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Tester">
  <data key="d0">Tester</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">A Tester is a role or individual involved in software testing. Testers are responsible for identifying the items being tested and describing the environment in which the test is conducted. The tester selects input data and executes software with the primary goal of detecting defects. This involves executing tests, reporting defects, and maintaining detailed records, including dates and names of test log authors for each event and activity.

A Tester may employ various testing techniques. Some testers approach the software-under-test as a "black box," utilizing methods like equivalence class partitioning to select test inputs. Other testers perform ad-hoc testing, which requires complete knowledge of the system being tested. A Tester is also expected to use past experience and intuition to design test cases, particularly when using the Error Guessing technique. Furthermore, a tester may contribute to the development of a test plan, collaborating with the project manager for input and alignment.&lt;SEP&gt;An individual responsible for running tests on items.&lt;SEP&gt;A Tester is responsible for analyzing test results, using tools, cooperating with various roles, and staying updated on technologies in software testing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-576c3b5853abc31c233b7f55290db336&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9ea23d51412441d95fd9957313b3d478&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ff3bcd5d811cf1d3238112df22f24549&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1f50a0acff86b61f2aebdc6201bedb80&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0c000d3c006e3afe689c5531f61cede1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e67f594ae3047aebaed5c7bf8c5ee26&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2b3c34fc8c737800e72c4ba3dd2c8eff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d54ee8dd0e2b5ff1654ab561620b6c44&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac3c02729685274cd9387cadef0dc333&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-09aff991601cb8d11a8b32035d5ed5c8</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831750</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Information">
  <data key="d0">Information</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Information about test execution gets collected in test logs and other files.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-576c3b5853abc31c233b7f55290db336</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830477</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Senior Management">
  <data key="d0">Senior Management</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Senior management receives insights from the test summary report about the fitness of the product for release.&lt;SEP&gt;Senior Management is responsible for recognizing and rewarding testing professionals within an organization.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-576c3b5853abc31c233b7f55290db336&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dfa4585fbbedcc4f123eb8d583c669ea</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831507</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Defect Identification">
  <data key="d0">Defect Identification</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Defect identification is an evidence of what defects exist in the product, their severity and impact.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-576c3b5853abc31c233b7f55290db336</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830479</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Test Item/Transmittal Report">
  <data key="d0">Test Item/Transmittal Report</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">The Test Item/Transmittal Report is associated with the items being tested.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-576c3b5853abc31c233b7f55290db336</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830480</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Operating System">
  <data key="d0">Operating System</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Operating system details are part of the environment description in the test log.&lt;SEP&gt;Operating System affects the compatibility of a product.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-576c3b5853abc31c233b7f55290db336&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac6e3a12af74abf6be605f347823c7a8</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831110</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Configuration Management Repository">
  <data key="d0">Configuration Management Repository</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">The configuration management repository is where the test plan is baselined for version control and consistency.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-976050e1c7ac2fe8f9cfeac3ea4fb575</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830490</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Testing Team">
  <data key="d0">Testing Team</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The testing team is responsible for designing the test case specification.&lt;SEP&gt;The Testing Team is a group responsible for traditional testing, which can be complemented by ad-hoc testing.&lt;SEP&gt;The Testing Team is a group responsible for software testing, with various organizational structures and reporting lines.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-976050e1c7ac2fe8f9cfeac3ea4fb575&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9ea23d51412441d95fd9957313b3d478&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-adc0f944e298fc1492f619b8a593d383</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831235</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Traceability Matrix">
  <data key="d0">Traceability Matrix</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">The traceability matrix is a tool created during the requirements gathering phase to validate that every requirement is tested, linking requirements to test cases.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-976050e1c7ac2fe8f9cfeac3ea4fb575</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830491</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Automation">
  <data key="d0">Automation</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Automation refers to the process of using automated tools to execute tests, requiring test scripts in an automation language.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-976050e1c7ac2fe8f9cfeac3ea4fb575&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4eb81c1b056c3ffba100a30fb6ddc42f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830492</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Manual Testing">
  <data key="d0">Manual Testing</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Manual testing involves executing tests step-by-step and validating the results manually.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-976050e1c7ac2fe8f9cfeac3ea4fb575&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac3c02729685274cd9387cadef0dc333</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830492</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Test Scripts">
  <data key="d0">Test Scripts</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Test scripts are written in an automation language for automated testing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-976050e1c7ac2fe8f9cfeac3ea4fb575</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830492</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Requirements Gathering Phase">
  <data key="d0">Requirements Gathering Phase</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">The requirements gathering phase is when the traceability matrix is created.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-976050e1c7ac2fe8f9cfeac3ea4fb575</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830494</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Automation Tool">
  <data key="d0">Automation Tool</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">The automation tool is used for automating test cases, and its cost is considered in the decision-making process.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-976050e1c7ac2fe8f9cfeac3ea4fb575</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830494</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Test Specifications">
  <data key="d0">Test Specifications</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">The test specifications are translated into a form from which the tests can be executed during test case development.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-976050e1c7ac2fe8f9cfeac3ea4fb575</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830494</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Test Case Development">
  <data key="d0">Test Case Development</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Test case development involves translating test specifications into executable tests.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-976050e1c7ac2fe8f9cfeac3ea4fb575</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830495</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Lock">
  <data key="d0">Lock</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">A lock is a device made of metal with a hole and key insertion facility for securing something.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fd156cdc428160086f8586613843cba1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830496</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Key">
  <data key="d0">Key</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">A key is a metal object designed to fit into a specific lock's keyhole to operate it.&lt;SEP&gt;Key is an input used in test cases to change the state from locked to unlocked and vice versa.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fd156cdc428160086f8586613843cba1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1d2b4e5470a5fae4ac0a621246515793</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830541</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Black Box Testing">
  <data key="d0">Black Box Testing</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Black Box Testing is a testing method done based on requirements, encompassing the end-user perspective and handling valid/invalid inputs.&lt;SEP&gt;Black box testing is a test strategy where the internal workings of the software are unknown to the tester. It relies on specifications, requirements, and domain knowledge to design test cases.&lt;SEP&gt;Black Box Testing is a testing technique used in Alpha Testing.&lt;SEP&gt;Black box testing is a testing method where the internal structure of the software is unknown to the tester.&lt;SEP&gt;Black Box Testing is a testing method where the internal structure of the item being tested is unknown to the tester.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fd156cdc428160086f8586613843cba1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4236e7b8427ccbaff16d4b0ef1506341&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d01d5a91698d48273a7f4da4a262d5a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-adc0f944e298fc1492f619b8a593d383&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-226d94c07ca09316fdcba5b872e40b9d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831574</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Random Testing">
  <data key="d0">Random Testing</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Random Testing is a testing approach that randomly selects test cases to eliminate tester biases.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fd156cdc428160086f8586613843cba1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830498</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Module">
  <data key="d0">Module</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">A module in the context of testing refers to a component with a valid input domain, used as an example for testing integers from 1 to 100.&lt;SEP&gt;A module is a distinct, self-contained part of a software system.&lt;SEP&gt;The module allows a user to perform a search for a character in an existing string.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fd156cdc428160086f8586613843cba1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ef2e90aeeaaea52d08d7eed63146a5f5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dadd5fedffda581a4f86164ce8358084</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831823</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Requirements Based Testing">
  <data key="d0">Requirements Based Testing</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Requirements Based Testing involves validating the requirements given in the Software Requirement Specifications (SRC).</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fd156cdc428160086f8586613843cba1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830499</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Software Requirement Specifications">
  <data key="d0">Software Requirement Specifications</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">The Software Requirement Specifications (SRC) are documents that contain explicit requirements stated for the software.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fd156cdc428160086f8586613843cba1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830500</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Requirements Traceability Matrix">
  <data key="d0">Requirements Traceability Matrix</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">A Requirements Traceability Matrix (RTM) tracks all requirements from genesis through design, development, and testing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fd156cdc428160086f8586613843cba1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830501</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="States">
  <data key="d0">States</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">States refers to the different conditions a lock can be in, specifically locked and unlocked.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fd156cdc428160086f8586613843cba1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830501</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Input">
  <data key="d0">Input</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Input refers to actions performed on the lock and key, such as turning the key clockwise and anticlockwise.&lt;SEP&gt;Input represents the data or signals fed into a system, influencing its behavior and state transitions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fd156cdc428160086f8586613843cba1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-413abe27441aa74b0b434e98bea575fe</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830872</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Output">
  <data key="d0">Output</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Output refers to the expected outcome of actions performed on the lock and key, specifically locking and unlocking.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fd156cdc428160086f8586613843cba1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830503</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Algorithmic and Processing Defects">
  <data key="d0">Algorithmic and Processing Defects</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Algorithmic and Processing Defects occur when processing steps in the algorithm, as described by the pseudo code, are incorrect.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9f460ca10683bf9cef13145da1c4fc71</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830514</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Control, Logic, and Sequence Defects">
  <data key="d0">Control, Logic, and Sequence Defects</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Control, Logic, and Sequence Defects occur when logic flow in the pseudo code is not correct.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9f460ca10683bf9cef13145da1c4fc71</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830514</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Data Defects">
  <data key="d0">Data Defects</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Data Defects are associated with incorrect design of data structures.&lt;SEP&gt;Data defects relate to an incorrect value for elements, such as the coin_values array.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9f460ca10683bf9cef13145da1c4fc71&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-00fde9a7a0d6d603361efdace01d913f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831635</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Module Interface Description Defects">
  <data key="d0">Module Interface Description Defects</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Module Interface Description Defects derive from using incorrect, and/or inconsistent parameter types, an incorrect number of parameters, or an incorrect ordering of parameters.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9f460ca10683bf9cef13145da1c4fc71</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830515</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Functional Description Defects">
  <data key="d0">Functional Description Defects</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Functional Description Defects include incorrect, missing, and/or unclear design elements.&lt;SEP&gt;Functional Description Defects are defects that arise because the functional description is ambiguous and incomplete.&lt;SEP&gt;Functional Description Defects are inaccuracies, ambiguities, or incompleteness in the overall description of the product's functionality and behavior.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9f460ca10683bf9cef13145da1c4fc71&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89e0667e9e77a3e174bbf9f89dd8f482&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90608f1fe255e95bf5a4da4744ec4c35</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831796</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="External Interface Description Defects">
  <data key="d0">External Interface Description Defects</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">External Interface Description Defects are derived from incorrect design descriptions for interfaces with COTS components, external software systems, databases, and hardware devices.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9f460ca10683bf9cef13145da1c4fc71</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830516</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Coding Defects">
  <data key="d0">Coding Defects</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Coding Defects are derived from errors in implementing the code.&lt;SEP&gt;Coding defects are errors that occur during the coding phase of software development.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9f460ca10683bf9cef13145da1c4fc71&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-00fde9a7a0d6d603361efdace01d913f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831636</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Total Coin Value">
  <data key="d0">Total Coin Value</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Total Coin Value represents the cumulative value of coins and is an integer.&lt;SEP&gt;Total Coin Value is an integer variable representing the calculated total value of all coins.&lt;SEP&gt;Total_coin_value is a variable that is not initialized before use, leading to a data flow defect.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-89e0667e9e77a3e174bbf9f89dd8f482&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7814e3a12bbf4d4dc88df26f6fc2b9f0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-00fde9a7a0d6d603361efdace01d913f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831641</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Number Of Notes">
  <data key="d0">Number Of Notes</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Number Of Notes represents the number of notes and is initialized to 0.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-89e0667e9e77a3e174bbf9f89dd8f482</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830517</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Pseudo Code">
  <data key="d0">Pseudo Code</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Pseudo Code is used to describe the processing steps in algorithms.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9f460ca10683bf9cef13145da1c4fc71</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830517</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Number Of Rupees">
  <data key="d0">Number Of Rupees</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Number Of Rupees represents the number of rupees, is initialized to 0, and is derived from the total coin value.&lt;SEP&gt;Number Of Rupees is an integer variable representing the number of rupees calculated from the total coin value.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-89e0667e9e77a3e174bbf9f89dd8f482&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7814e3a12bbf4d4dc88df26f6fc2b9f0</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831169</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Number Of Paise">
  <data key="d0">Number Of Paise</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Number Of Paise represents the number of paise, is initialized to 0, and is derived from the total coin value.&lt;SEP&gt;Number Of Paise is an integer variable representing the remaining paise after calculating the number of rupees.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-89e0667e9e77a3e174bbf9f89dd8f482&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7814e3a12bbf4d4dc88df26f6fc2b9f0</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831170</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Coin Values">
  <data key="d0">Coin Values</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Coin Values is an array containing the values: 1, 5, 10, 25, 25, 100.&lt;SEP&gt;Coin Values is an array of six integers representing the value of each coin in cents: 1, 5, 10, 25, 25, 100.&lt;SEP&gt;Coin_values is an integer array that should contain the values 1, 5, 10, 25, 50, 100.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-89e0667e9e77a3e174bbf9f89dd8f482&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7814e3a12bbf4d4dc88df26f6fc2b9f0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-00fde9a7a0d6d603361efdace01d913f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831635</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Number Of Coins">
  <data key="d0">Number Of Coins</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Number Of Coins represents the input and cannot be negative.&lt;SEP&gt;Number Of Coins is an integer variable representing the quantity of coins entered by the user.&lt;SEP&gt;Number_of_coins is a variable for which the address must be provided when calling "scanf".</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-89e0667e9e77a3e174bbf9f89dd8f482&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7814e3a12bbf4d4dc88df26f6fc2b9f0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-00fde9a7a0d6d603361efdace01d913f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831644</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Precondition">
  <data key="d0">Precondition</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A Precondition is a condition that must be true in order for a software component to operate properly; an example is `number_of_coins &gt;= 0`.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-89e0667e9e77a3e174bbf9f89dd8f482</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830521</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Postcondition">
  <data key="d0">Postcondition</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A Postcondition is a condition that must be true when a software component completes its operation properly; an example is `number_of_rupees, number_of_paises &gt;= 0`.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-89e0667e9e77a3e174bbf9f89dd8f482</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830522</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Design Defects">
  <data key="d0">Design Defects</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Design Defects are defects related to control, logic, and sequencing.&lt;SEP&gt;Design Defects occur when system components or their interactions are incorrectly designed.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-89e0667e9e77a3e174bbf9f89dd8f482&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90608f1fe255e95bf5a4da4744ec4c35</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831797</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="While Loop Condition">
  <data key="d0">While Loop Condition</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">While Loop Condition is related to control logic that requires a condition to be met for a loop to continue, should be less than or equal to six in the context of the given code.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-89e0667e9e77a3e174bbf9f89dd8f482</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830523</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Ad-Hoc Testing">
  <data key="d0">Ad-Hoc Testing</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Ad-Hoc Testing is a software testing method characterized by its unstructured approach and intent to find loopholes in the system.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9ea23d51412441d95fd9957313b3d478</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830534</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="SDLC">
  <data key="d0">SDLC</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">SDLC refers to the Software Development Life Cycle, where ad-hoc testing can be applied by developers.&lt;SEP&gt;SDLC refers to Software Development Life Cycle, used in tracking Effort Variance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9ea23d51412441d95fd9957313b3d478&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2e450de8294677410b0dfa671b57c74f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831400</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Documentation">
  <data key="d0">Documentation</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Documentation refers to the written records and procedures typically required in structured testing, which ad-hoc testing does not mandate.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9ea23d51412441d95fd9957313b3d478</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830536</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Architecture">
  <data key="d0">Architecture</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Architecture refers to the underlying structure and design of the system, which testers can focus on understanding during ad-hoc testing.&lt;SEP&gt;Architecture and characteristics of the machine (32 bit, 64 bit…) affects the compatibility of a product.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9ea23d51412441d95fd9957313b3d478&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac6e3a12af74abf6be605f347823c7a8</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831107</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Functional System Testing">
  <data key="d0">Functional System Testing</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Functional System Testing is a type of testing performed at different phases, focusing on product-level features.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9ea23d51412441d95fd9957313b3d478</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830537</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Product Level Features">
  <data key="d0">Product Level Features</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Product Level Features are the specific functionalities of the software being tested during functional system testing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9ea23d51412441d95fd9957313b3d478</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830537</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Duplication">
  <data key="d0">Duplication</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Duplication refers to the problem of performing the same tests multiple times during functional system testing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9ea23d51412441d95fd9957313b3d478</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830537</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Gray Area">
  <data key="d0">Gray Area</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Gray Area refers to the issue of certain tests being missed out in all phases of functional system testing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9ea23d51412441d95fd9957313b3d478</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830538</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Unit - II Page 6">
  <data key="d0">Unit - II Page 6</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Unit II Page 6 refers to a specific section of a document or course material on software testing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1d2b4e5470a5fae4ac0a621246515793</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830538</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
