<node id="Product">
  <data key="d0">Product</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Product is something tested for its features and behavior.&lt;SEP&gt;The product is the final deliverable of the software development process, of which system testing is performed on.&lt;SEP&gt;The product refers to the software-under-test, whose behavior is checked under various logical conditions of input variables.&lt;SEP&gt;The Product undergoes beta testing by customers to ensure it meets beta testing entry criteria.&lt;SEP&gt;The product refers to the software system that is being documented and tested.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-57b5bdf87e3c8352e48d198a65913eb1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ef2e90aeeaaea52d08d7eed63146a5f5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e67f594ae3047aebaed5c7bf8c5ee26&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-588cab56860b1b61b223c01b7307a5a5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e0b2f4de41f85e92858a47a98a81b2d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831616</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Defect Detection">
  <data key="d0">Defect Detection</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Defect detection is the focus of functional testing.&lt;SEP&gt;Defect Detection refers to the process of identifying errors or flaws in software or code.&lt;SEP&gt;Defect Detection is the process of identifying errors or defects in the software artifact.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-57b5bdf87e3c8352e48d198a65913eb1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-52bc934fcfeec89646ffbc42ac44a30a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c865455d56f087310ad4a2872dcee595</data>
