<node id="Integration Testing">
  <data key="d0">Integration Testing</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Integration Testing is testing the interaction between the modules and interaction with other systems externally.&lt;SEP&gt;Integration testing is the process of testing the interfaces between software components.&lt;SEP&gt;Integration Testing is a phase involving different activities and types of testing to ensure completeness and coverage for functionality.&lt;SEP&gt;Integration testing is the process of testing the interfaces between software components.&lt;SEP&gt;Integration testing is a software testing phase that combines individual software modules and tests them as a group.&lt;SEP&gt;Integration testing is a type of software testing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d95d5a03291c8ae4834c72b31a85edc7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ef2e90aeeaaea52d08d7eed63146a5f5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8230b787a8fe42514cbd735e327e0d20&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-adc0f944e298fc1492f619b8a593d383&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d4600873a7185719f33d700ae5a5d121&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-994f0b8030636c42759ae6d6ee2baddc</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831474</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Internal Interfaces">
  <data key="d0">Internal Interfaces</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Internal Interfaces are communication across two modules within a project or product, internal to the product, and not exposed to the customer or external developers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d95d5a03291c8ae4834c72b31a85edc7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830634</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="External Interfaces">
  <data key="d0">External Interfaces</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">External Interfaces are visible outside the product to third party developers and solution providers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d95d5a03291c8ae4834c72b31a85edc7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830635</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Application Programming Interfaces">
