<node id="Black Box Test Design">
  <data key="d0">Black Box Test Design</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Black box test design is a strategy where test cases are created based on the specifications and requirements of the software unit.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0682a23253488e1a8adf8e634de7e049</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830688</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="White Box Test Design">
  <data key="d0">White Box Test Design</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">White box test design is a strategy where test cases are created based on the internal structure and code of the software unit.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0682a23253488e1a8adf8e634de7e049</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830689</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Test Harness">
  <data key="d0">Test Harness</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A test harness is a collection of drivers and stubs used to support and automate the testing of software units.&lt;SEP&gt;Test harness is a tool used in unit testing.&lt;SEP&gt;Test Harness is supplementary code that is written specifically to support the test efforts.&lt;SEP&gt;A Test Harness is auxiliary code developed to test software, particularly at the unit and integration levels.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0682a23253488e1a8adf8e634de7e049&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-08aa6af3aad54d106fc55a5710f36151&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-750a18a20f82fd7a983c3b7f203c7a6f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7814e3a12bbf4d4dc88df26f6fc2b9f0</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831167</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Drivers">
  <data key="d0">Drivers</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Drivers are components of a test harness that call the target code being tested.&lt;SEP&gt;Drivers are dummy programs that call functions of the lowest module when the calling function does not exist.&lt;SEP&gt;Drivers are software modules used in bottom-up testing to simulate the behavior of higher-level components.&lt;SEP&gt;Drivers are software modules used to replace calling modules in testing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0682a23253488e1a8adf8e634de7e049&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-08aa6af3aad54d106fc55a5710f36151&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4a2a0fc342861ce4f51a3e5784bf82da&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d4600873a7185719f33d700ae5a5d121</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831341</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Stubs">
  <data key="d0">Stubs</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Stubs are components of a test harness that represent modules called by the target code.&lt;SEP&gt;Stubs are code snippets that accept inputs/requests from a top module and return results/responses when lower modules are unavailable.&lt;SEP&gt;Stubs are software modules used in top-down testing to simulate the behavior of lower-level components.&lt;SEP&gt;Stubs are software modules used to replace called modules in testing.&lt;SEP&gt;Stubs are used in testing to simulate the behavior of called components.</data>
