<node id="Mean Time To Discover The Next K Faults">
  <data key="d0">Mean Time To Discover The Next K Faults</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Mean Time To Discover The Next K Faults is a measure used to predict the average time until the next K faults are encountered in a product.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0bc02d92c94be7170edbcd55893256aa</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770830983</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Stress Testing">
  <data key="d0">Stress Testing</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Stress Testing is a method used to evaluate a system beyond specified requirements to ensure it does not break under extreme conditions.&lt;SEP&gt;Stress Testing is a testing method in which tests for stress are selected based on certain guidelines.&lt;SEP&gt;Stress Testing assesses the limits of a system by subjecting it to high loads.&lt;SEP&gt;Stress testing is a type of testing that is amenable to automation, focusing on evaluating system performance under extreme conditions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0bc02d92c94be7170edbcd55893256aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ba6b80bf01467ce55688de3f4b3e1921&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4eb81c1b056c3ffba100a30fb6ddc42f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f9a1e0b0e37c96741aefa49dc8030cdc</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831782</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
