<node id="White Box Testing">
  <data key="d0">White Box Testing</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">White box testing is a test strategy where the tester has knowledge of the internal workings of the software, including design and code. It uses methods like statement, branch, and path testing.&lt;SEP&gt;A testing approach that examines and tests the internal program code to verify its functionality.&lt;SEP&gt;White Box Testing is a testing technique used in Alpha Testing.&lt;SEP&gt;White box testing is a testing method where the internal structure of the software is known to the tester.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4236e7b8427ccbaff16d4b0ef1506341&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dbc728752df68dcf9cf8ae1e0942cee8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d01d5a91698d48273a7f4da4a262d5a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-adc0f944e298fc1492f619b8a593d383</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831239</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="State Transition Testing">
  <data key="d0">State Transition Testing</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">State Transition Testing is a black box testing method that tests the transitions between different states of the software.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4236e7b8427ccbaff16d4b0ef1506341</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831043</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
