<node id="Onsite Deployment">
  <data key="d0">Onsite Deployment</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Onsite Deployment is a type of Deployment Testing conducted after the release of the product at the customer’s location, with the combined effort of the product development organization and the customer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9d01d5a91698d48273a7f4da4a262d5a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831188</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Online Deployment Testing">
  <data key="d0">Online Deployment Testing</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Online Deployment Testing is Deployment testing done in two stages, using mirrored systems with data from the live system.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9d01d5a91698d48273a7f4da4a262d5a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831188</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Alpha Testing">
  <data key="d0">Alpha Testing</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Alpha Testing involves white and black box testing techniques, where company employees, independent test teams, potential end users, and stakeholders test the software for functionality and provide feedback. It is often used for COTS software.&lt;SEP&gt;Alpha Testing is performed at the developing organization's location with developers involved.&lt;SEP&gt;Alpha Testing is performed by developers and sometimes an Independent Testing Team at the software development site.&lt;SEP&gt;Alpha Testing is internal acceptance testing performed by members within the developing organization.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9d01d5a91698d48273a7f4da4a262d5a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-72174c906a600ada847dff60ecc94505&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-588cab56860b1b61b223c01b7307a5a5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-226d94c07ca09316fdcba5b872e40b9d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831574</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Software QA Team">
  <data key="d0">Software QA Team</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Software QA team performs additional testing in the second phase of Alpha Testing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9d01d5a91698d48273a7f4da4a262d5a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770831192</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
